Introduction
=============
Kubernetes:
1) it is an open-source orchestration and management tools for containers.

	(Note: orchestration tools means centralize management.)

IMQ) Before orchestration tool what was the challenges in containers.
1) no centralize management.
2) No clustering/fail-over
3) Auto scalability

Advantages :-
==========
1) Centralized management for container Host: 
      a) now we are able to manage all docker machines/container host from single site/node)
      b) we can create/delete/upgrade containers.
                                      
2) HighAvailability 
We have two mode to run containers.
   a) standalone. ( no clustering/no fail-over)
   b) cluster mode.( more then two system work together, containers can migrate to other machines in fail-over)

Cluster Arch:
     a) if any docker machine goes down. all workload will be fail-over on another docker machine.
     b) it maintain your containers/node state as well. ( if any single container has problem, then KB8 try to recover it or create new one and also can migrate on another docker host.

3) scalability: increase/add the container to diatribe for existing running application.
   scalability are two types
   a) manually : 
   b) automatically :
 
   scalability are two type:
   a) vertical (extend the resource like CPU, ram on existing running containers.) 
   b) horizontal scaling ( add new containers in pool)

4) rollout(means upgrade version) and rollback(downgrade version/in previous version without downtime) application.( in zero time we can upgrade appllication)

