Kubernetes arch-:

Kubernetes cluster: 
  a) Set of docker machines which are working together and managed by Kubernetes server it call one cluster.
  They may be
  1) physical:
  2) virtualization 
        1) kvm/vmware Microsoft
        2) Cloud based

1) Kubernetes master nodes:
    => it an separate server which provide all management command for containers.
    => from this machines we can manage all containers host.

	Note: four services which away run on master node:

2) worker node: => the server/machine there we are creating container using Kubernetes/orchestration node.
                => the machine there we are running out application inside the containers.
                => the machines which managed by Kubernetes server.

Kubernetes master services:-
===========================
1) kube-api: 1) Any command which execute by administrator it goes to api first. 
             2) it does validation(authentication and authorization, like check user and what right he has) for any instruction. 

2) kube-etcd:1) it contains complete Kubernetes cluster information.
             2) it store api related information.
             3) it is yaml based database. it store data key: value format(yaml format)

3) kube-scheduler:1) decide best worker node(or healthy node) for your application Pods(containers).
                  
4) kube-controller:
          1) it maintain communication with worker node through api.
          2) it provide api instruction to worker node. (it give handover api command to worker node)

command flow

command=> API => Etcd => scheduler => controller = worker node:

worker node
1) this is container machine which controller by Kubernetes server.
2) docker machine has given his management to Kubernetes master.

1) container socket : 
	both socket developed by docker community based.
	a) dockerd
	b) containerd
	
	Redhat/IBM
        c) cri-io

2)  Kubelet: it is Kubernetes Agent which take command from  kube-controller.
	1) it is agent of kubernetes master which need to run on each worker-node.
	2) without kubelet kubernetes can not controller your container host.
	3) it take instruction and executed which given by kube-controller.

User--command--API---etcd--scheduler--controller---- (WorkerNode)--kubelet--containerd/dockerd/cri-io

Note: dockerd now not in use too much


3) kube-proxy: it manage your container traffice layer work.



